From: Aaron Fainshtein <aaronfainshtein1@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 18 May 2026
Subject: [PATCH] fix(cli): use stdin fd 0 instead of /dev/stdin path for Windows compat

The CLI and report command read stdin via `readFileSync('/dev/stdin', ...)`,
which works on macOS/Linux but fails on Windows (Git Bash, PowerShell, cmd)
with ENOENT because Windows doesn't expose /dev/stdin as a filesystem path.

Node and Bun both accept fd 0 (process.stdin's fd) as the first argument to
readFileSync, and the behavior is identical across platforms. This is a
one-character change in two locations.

Repro on Windows:
  $ echo "hello" | gbrain put test-page
  ENOENT: no such file or directory, open '/dev/stdin'

After this patch:
  $ echo "hello" | gbrain put test-page
  { "slug": "test-page", "status": "created_or_updated", "chunks": 1 }

---
 src/cli.ts              | 2 +-
 src/commands/report.ts  | 2 +-
 2 files changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/cli.ts b/src/cli.ts
index abcdef0..1234567 100644
--- a/src/cli.ts
+++ b/src/cli.ts
@@ -134,7 +134,7 @@
 
   // Read stdin for content params
   if (op.cliHints?.stdin && !params[op.cliHints.stdin] && !process.stdin.isTTY) {
-    const stdinContent = readFileSync('/dev/stdin', 'utf-8');
+    const stdinContent = readFileSync(0, 'utf-8');
     const MAX_STDIN = 5_000_000; // 5MB
     if (Buffer.byteLength(stdinContent, 'utf-8') > MAX_STDIN) {
       console.error(`Error: stdin content exceeds ${MAX_STDIN} bytes. Split into smaller inputs.`);
diff --git a/src/commands/report.ts b/src/commands/report.ts
index fedcba0..7654321 100644
--- a/src/commands/report.ts
+++ b/src/commands/report.ts
@@ -41,7 +41,7 @@
   // Read content from --content arg or stdin
   let content = contentIdx >= 0 ? args[contentIdx + 1] : null;
   if (!content && !process.stdin.isTTY) {
-    content = readFileSync('/dev/stdin', 'utf-8');
+    content = readFileSync(0, 'utf-8');
   }
 
   if (!content?.trim()) {
-- 
2.49.0
